    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n      <strong>School:</strong>&nbsp;evocation&nbsp;[light];\n    <br>\n    <strong>Level:</strong>&nbsp;Cleric 3, Sorcerer 2, Wizard 2;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    <br>\n    <strong>Components:</strong>&nbsp;V, S, M (you sprinkle ruby dust (worth 50 gp) on the item that is to carry the flame)<br>\n    \n      <strong>Casting Time:</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Range:</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Target:</strong>&nbsp;object touched; magical, heatless flame\n<br>\n    <strong>Effect:</strong>&nbsp;Object touched; Magical, heatless flame\n<br>\n    <strong>Duration:</strong>&nbsp;Permanent<br>\n    \n        <strong>Saving Throw:</strong>&nbsp;None\n\n        <br>\n        <strong>Spell Resistance:</strong>&nbsp;no<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  \n\n\n<p>\nA flame, equivalent in brightness to a torch, springs forth from an object that you touch. The effect looks like a regular flame, but it creates no heat and doesn’t use oxygen. A <i>continual flame </i>can be covered and hidden but not smothered or quenched.\n</p><p>Light spells counter and dispel darkness spells of an equal or lower level.\n</p><p><i>Material Component: </i>You sprinkle ruby dust (worth 50 gp) on the item that is to carry the flame.\n</p>\n<hr/>\n\n\n\n</div>\n",
